Iris Flower Classification

Project Overview
This project is a supervised machine learning model that classifies iris flowers into three species based on sepal and petal measurements.

The model predicts:
- Setosa
- Versicolor
- Virginica

 Objective
To build a classification model using the Iris dataset and evaluate its performance using standard machine learning techniques.

Dataset
Dataset Used: Iris Dataset  
Features:
- Sepal Length
- Sepal Width
- Petal Length
- Petal Width

Target:
- Flower Species
 Technologies Used
- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Scikit-learn
- Matplotlib

Steps Performed
1. Data Loading
2. Data Exploration & Visualization
3. Train-Test Split
4. Model Training (Logistic Regression / KNN / Decision Tree)
5. Model Evaluation using Accuracy Score & Confusion Matrix

Results
Achieved 95%+ accuracy on test dataset.

 How to Run
1. Install required libraries:
   pip install pandas numpy scikit-learn matplotlib

2. Run the Python file:
   python iris_model.py

